lays.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"details\",\"Can I use this on an exam?\",{\"className\":\"group\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"summary\",null,{\"className\":\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-medium text-foreground hover:text-brand\",\"children\":\"Can I use this on an exam?\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"That depends on your instructor's policy. Many allow browser-based calculators for online exams. This tool runs entirely in your browser with no server communication, so it works offline after the initial load.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"details\",\"Why not just use Desmos?\",{\"className\":\"group\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"summary\",null,{\"className\":\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-medium text-foreground hover:text-brand\",\"children\":\"Why not just use Desmos?\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Desmos is excellent for graphing but doesn't include statistics (regression, distributions) or matrix operations. If your textbook references TI-84 workflows (STAT > CALC > LinReg, DISTR > normalcdf), this tool follows those same workflows with a modern UI.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"details\",\"Does it save my work?\",{\"className\":\"group\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"summary\",null,{\"className\":\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-medium text-foreground hover:text-brand\",\"children\":\"Does it save my work?\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Yes. Your functions, data lists, matrices, and settings are automatically saved to your browser's localStorage and restored when you return.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"details\",\"What functions does the expression parser support?\",{\"className\":\"group\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"summary\",null,{\"className\":\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-medium text-foreground hover:text-brand\",\"children\":\"What functions does the expression parser support?\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Standard arithmetic (+, -, *, /, ^), trig (sin, cos, tan, asin, acos, atan), logarithms (log, ln, log10, log2), exponentials (exp, e^x), roots (sqrt, cbrt), and more. Constants pi and e are built in.\"}]]}]]}]]}]\n39:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Confusing the negation key with subtraction\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"On TI-style calculators, (−)3² gives −9, not 9, because the negation binds looser than the exponent. Wrap negatives in parentheses for clarity: (−3)².\"}]]}]\n3a:[\"$\",\"li\",\"Forgetting implicit multiplication\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L5\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$34:1:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-pink-500\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Forgetting implicit multiplication\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"2(3) and 2·3 both work; 2x means 2 times x. But 2sin(x) is sometimes parsed differently than 2·sin(x). When in doubt, insert the multiplication explicitly.\"}]]}]]}]\n3b:[\"$\",\"li\",\"Reading the wrong intersection\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L5\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$34:1:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-pink-500\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Reading the wrong intersection\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"When two curves cross multiple times, the calculate→intersect tool returns the nearest intersection to the cursor position. Move the cursor close to the intersection you actually want.\"}]]}]]}]\n3c:[\"$\",\"li\",\"Using degree mode for derivatives\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L5\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$34:1:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-pink-500\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Using degree mode for derivatives\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Calculus on trig functions assumes radians. Compute d/dx[sin(x)] in degree mode and you'll get π/180 of the expected answer.\"}]]}]]}]\n3d:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"aria-labelledby\":\"tool-insights-takeaways\",\"className\":\"rounded-lg border border-brand/30 bg-brand/5 p-5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"id\":\"tool-insights-takeaways\",\"className\":\"text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight\",\"children\":\"Key Takeaways\"}],[\"$\",\"ul\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-3 space-y-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"The Graphing Calculator replicates the TI-84 Plus CE workflow with full keyboard navigation.\",{\"className\":\"flex items-start gap-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L5\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":[[\"circle\",{\"cx\":\"12\",\"cy\":\"12\",\"r\":\"10\",\"key\":\"1mglay\"}],[\"path\",{\"d\":\"m9 12 2 2 4-4\",\"key\":\"dzmm74\"}]],\"className\":\"lucide-circle-check mt-0.5 size-4 shrink-0 text-brand\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm text-foreground\",\"children\":\"The Graphing Calculator replicates the TI-84 Plus CE workflow with full keyboard navigation.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"It supports function plotting, parametric/polar